<br>
It makes a big difference if the AA mana regen skill is just another buff like clairity vs. an increase in your BASE regen rate since I don't think clairity and other buffs are helped by medding. I don't plan on expending 12 AA points to max out mana regen if it doesn't really increase the base rate of mana regen and is really just a low rent breeze.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uchitlinsoulfood.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chitlin Soulfood</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://eq.kalie.net/sigs/chitlin-itty.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Ol' Dirty Dawg</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/13/02 12:30:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fbrellserilisbrellserilisdiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10715.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eq.kalie.net/sigs/chitlin-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: AA Mana Regen Archetype Skill Question</span><hr size=1> From what I understand, it's an intert increase in your *natural* base regen.<br>
<br>
50+ you'll get 1 mana/tic (natural regen) standing, 20 mana/tic medding. With three points in Mental Clarity you'd get 4 standing (very nice for hybrids) and 24 sitting (err, assuming a 250+ meditate skill, not sure what hybrids cap at). All FT items and buffs would then be added on top of that regen.<br>
<br>
As a druid, with Form of the Howler on I get 3 mana/tic regen - which is like having Mental Clarity (2). There's a noticable difference, but nothing to write home about.<br>
<br>
If you're a priest or an int caster MC alone won't make nearly the noticable difference most people expect. As a hybrid, it'll practically quadruple the mana regen you normally experience when not medding and in combat.<br>
<br>
The key though is stacking your possible regen points. By the time you get Mental Clarity pumped up you'll probably have access to at least FT1 items.<br>
<br>
Of course, I don't have it yet myself, someone correct me if I'm wrong in my assumptions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>
